<DOCNO> AP890407-0006 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a bomb left in a car exploded 
outside a government office in armagh injuring an elderly woman 
police said 
the office where drivers licenses are issued was badly damaged 
but was closed at the time belfast police said police did not 
identify the victim they said only that she was struck in the head 
by flying debris when the bomb believed to contain 250 pounds of 
explosives went off late thursday 
no group immediately claimed responsibility 
the mainly roman catholic irish republican army is fighting 
british rule in northern ireland it wants to unite the 
predominantly protestant province with the irish republic where 95 
percent of the population is catholic 
armagh 35 miles southwest of belfast is the religious center 
for ireland and is where the catholic and anglican primates of 
ireland have their seats 
until thursdays bombing the city had escaped most of the 
sectarian and political violence in northern ireland over the past 
20 years 
</TEXT>
