<DOCNO> AP890407-0007 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
demonstrations in which palestinians are injured 
are common these days during the 16month uprising in the occupied 
territories here is a detailed look at one of them 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the lieutenant chased the 
rockthrowing demonstrators through the dusty streets he turned 
down a corner off the main square and saw the palestinian youth in 
blue jeans and white sneakers he knelt and fired 
the youth fell blood rushing from his head theyve got a 
casualty the lieutenant shouted 
similar scenes of violence are repeated almost daily in the 
palestinian uprising in the west bank and gaza strip but this time 
the israeli soldiers opened fire in front of reporters and 
photographers 
in thursdays incident there were no warning shouts or shots in 
the air and the use of live ammunition seemed to conflict with 
army regulations 
four soldiers in a jeep rounded a corner into the demonstration 
they were met by about 100 demonstrators who were throwing rocks 
and bottles over roadblocks of flaming tires the soldiers opened 
fire almost immediately 
the victim 17yearold dahoud khaled nassar of bethlehem was 
unconscious and in criticial condition with two bullet wounds to 
the head according to doctors at mukassed hospital in jerusalem 
the lieutenant in his late 30s chased away a reporter and a 
television crew who moved toward the stricken youth he then joined 
another officer shooting after youths running down another narrow 
street in bethlehems madbasa quarter 
residents along the street picked up nassars limp body and took 
it in a car to nearby beit jala hospital doctors there ordered the 
victim transferred to the better equipped mukassed about six miles 
away in jerusalem 
an army spokesman who by military regulation is not identified 
confirmed one youth was shot in a violent confrontation with 
soldiers an initial investigation in the field shows that no 
live ammunition was fired we are continuing to investigate she 
said 
an official in the army spokesmans office who agreed to 
discuss army regulations on firing at demonstrators on condition of 
anonymity said soldiers can only use live ammunition when their 
lives are in danger 
he said soldiers can fire plastic bullets to disperse a violent 
domonstration even if their lives are not endangered but he said 
a soldier is only allowed to fire a plastic bullet at a fleeing 
suspect who has committed a serious offense such as a stabbing 
a soldier cant fire at someone running away if the guy has 
thrown a rock the official said 
after thursdays demonstration doctors said nassar was hit with 
two live rounds none of the soldiers was reported injured in the 
barrage of rocks and bottles 
the demonstration had started like many others about half an 
hour earlier in the commercial district its streets lined with 
shops restaurants and hotels that used to be crowded with pilgrims 
visiting this biblical city where jesus was born 
about 100 people men and women gathered in a small square 
they set up roadblocks of rocks and burning tires at three points 
to block off the area many had their faces covered with checkered 
arab keffiyeh headresses or scarves in the red green black and 
white colors of the outlawed palestinian flag 
they carried a flag too and chanted allahu akbar god is 
great long live the flag they also shouted plo israel no 
and popular revolution against the zionists 
some of the leaders of the chants seemed to be reading them off 
pieces of paper as they shouted women in the crowd gathered rocks 
from the street putting them in buckets at street corners in 
expectation that soldiers might come 
they came four of them in a jeep after the crowd had been 
marching and chanting for about a half hour 
as is usually the case the crowd of masked protesters unleashed 
rocks and empty bottles at the intruders some used slingshots to 
fire stones at the soldiers 
the four soldiers began shooting with rifles almost immediately 
after the jeep stopped with a captain in dark glasses firing from 
the drivers seat 
israeli and foreign photographers and a young arab boy wheeling 
a bicycle who was not part of the protest dived for cover 
then the soldiers still firing began chasing the fleeing 
demonstrators through the surrounding streets three of the troops 
headed down a road to the west and the lieutenant ran after nassar 
on a street to the east 
unlike the others nassar had no scarf covering his face 
after rounding the corner from the square the lieutenant knelt 
with one knee on the dusty pavement amid stones from a roadblock 
placed by the protesters he took careful aim and two shots could 
be heard 
about 40 yards away nassar fell to the ground bleeding from 
behind his right ear 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

