<TEXT>
pulitzer prizewinning author and 
astronomer carl sagan says the united states and the soviet union 
should join forces and head for mars 
the show of cooperation between the two superpowers could revive 
a space exploration program that has been dormant for 10 years 
sagan told more than 400 scientists and aerospace specialists 
gathered wednesday for a symposium 
sagan joked that the joint mission might trigger a dispute over 
who would get to set foot first on mars i have one solution 
sagan said we tie together the ankles of the soviet and us 
astronauts or perhaps a better solution posed by the europeans 
let them be first 
sagan told reporters after his speech that he thinks heading to 
mars is a better next step for space exploration than establishing 
a presence on the moon 
the moon worries me sagan said the moon is dull weve 
been to the moon it is unchanging people are fundamentally 
bored with it 
mars on the other hand is a dynamic world it has weather 
it has climatic change it is something that will occupy our 
exploratory sense for a great period of time 
</TEXT>
