grandfathers release 
eaton county prosecutor g michael hocking started asking 
questions when a sheriffs deputy gave a ride home to an old man he 
met march 24 in an eaton rapids market the man introduced himself 
as mel henwood 
its kind of scary its especially scary when you think that 
fathers day is getting closer hocking said 
under michigan law people who sign voluntary commitment papers 
void their courtordered treatment thats what henwood did blunt 
said adding we were very surprised when they allowed him to 
