<TEXT>
the government today charged five more 
sikhs including a former police superintendent in the 1984 
assassination of prime minister indira gandhi 
investigators appointed by the government to find out who 
plotted mrs gandhis murder filed 10 charges against each person 
including murder attempted murder criminal conspiracy sedition 
and waging or attempting to wage war against the state 
conviction carries a maximum punishment of death by hanging two 
sikhs already have been executed in the case including one of the 
bodyguards who shot mrs gandhi 
the government said the five sikhs conspired to destabilize 
india after a june 1984 army raid on the golden temple the holiest 
sikh shrine 
the former senior superintendent of police simranjeet singh 
mann resigned after the army raid the others named were jagmohan 
singh tony and dalip singh both college lecturers in bombay and 
attinder pal singh one of the most notorious sikh militants 
mann and attinder pal singh are in custody and officials said 
warrants have been issued for tony and dalip singh who are 
believed to be in bombay 
the fifth sikh named in the charges rattan singh was killed by 
rival sikh militants in 1985 the government said 
none of the sikhs were related all sikh males take the name 
singh which means lion in the punjabi language 
the indian express the countrys largest selling 
englishlanguage newspaper today reported the five sikhs 
established contact with mrs gandhis two known assassins through 
balbir singh a sikh employed in the prime ministers security 
network 
however the newspaper said balbir singh could not be charged 
again because he was acquitted of conspiracy charges in the 
assassination by the supreme court last august 
balbir singh was earlier found guilty and sentenced to hang by a 
trial court but the supreme court overturned the conviction for 
lack of evidence 
mrs gandhi was gunned down by two sikh bodyguards in the garden 
of her new delhi residence on oct 31 1984 one of the assassins 
was shot and killed by other bodyguards and the other was convicted 
and hanged on jan 6 
a third sikh kehar singh was convicted on conspiracy charges 
and also hanged jan 6 
sikhs make up 2 percent of indias population sikh militants 
who claim discrimination by the hindu majority have been fighting 
since 1982 for a separate nation 
