<TEXT>
the government friday charged five sikhs 
with conspiracy in the assassination of prime minister indira 
gandhi in 1984 which it said was part of a plot to establish a 
separate sikh nation 
one defendant rattan singh was killed by rival sikh militants 
in 1985 the government said the others are simranjeet singh mann 
a former senior police officer attinder pal singh a wellknown 
militant and college lecturers dalip singh and jagmohan singh tony 
officers of the special investigating team examining the case 
filed the charges with sl khanna chief magistrate of new delhi 
all five are accused of waging war aginst the state sedition 
criminal conspiracy murder and attempted murder the charges carry 
the death penalty 
beant singh and and satwant singh sikh members of mrs gandhis 
personal guard shot her down oct 31 1984 in her new delhi 
residence beant singh was killed by other bodyguards and satwant 
singh was hanged jan 6 
also hanged was kehar singh an uncle of beant singh who was 
convicted of conspiracy 
none of the other singhs are related all male sikhs take the 
name singh which means lion in punjabi as a doctrine of their 
faith 
the government said the five began plotting after the army raid 
mrs gandhi ordered in june 1984 on sikhisms holiest shrine the 
golden temple in amritsar 
its list of charges gave this account of the defendants 
activities 
they conspired to commit sensational acts in order to create 
chaos confusion and anarchy by hijacking planes breaching canals 
poisoning drinking water supply and destroying parliament house 
those acts included organizing the hijacking of an indian 
airlines plane to dubai on aug 24 1984 they planned to kill mrs 
gandhi and her son rajiv who succeeded her as prime minister in 
september in nagpur central india but the assassination 
could not be executed for want of weapons 
mann and attinder pal singh decided to attempt the murder 
through someone associated with mrs gandhis security and 
attinder pal singh located subinspector beant singh as the most 
suitable person the government said 
attinder pal singh fled to pakistan a week before the 
assassination where he was given a free hand to enlist support 
for a separate sikh nation in punjab the only indian state where 
sikhs are the majority 
he also was allowed to provide arms for training sikh youth 
and contact foreignbased activists for financial help according 
to the government 
it did not elaborate on the militants alleged links to 
pakistan but india often accuses the pakistanis of supporting sikh 
secessionists no proof has been offered and pakistan which 
borders punjab denies it 
mann was arrested in december 1984 while trying to flee to nepal 
and attinder pal singh was apprehended in october 1988 
while in custody mann was named president of the unified akali 
dal a militant sikh political party in punjab a northern state 
that is indias richest agricultural region 
he resigned as a senior superintendent of police to protest the 
raid on the golden temple whose purpose was to dislodge militants 
who had turned the shrine into a fortress at least 1200 people 
were killed in the assault 
only 2 percent of indias 880 million people are sikhs they 
accuse hindus who make up 90 percent of discrimination 
sikh militants began fighting for a separate nation in 1982 at 
least 2400 people were killed in 1988 and more than 500 people 
have been slain so far this year 
