a sharp earthquake jolted southern 
california from downtown los angeles to san diego on friday 
causing minor injuries and damage in orange county where the 
shaking was strongest 
mirrors windows and wine bottles smashed to floors at fashion 
island shopping center the largest outdoor mall in orange county 
said anita hilyer administrative director she said shoppers 
scrambled when the 46magnitude temblor hit 
some of them panicked and got in their cars and tried to get 
out of here she said some went to the center of the mall to 
wait and see and what would happen next 
several people were injured by broken glass at rjs the rib 
joint restaurant in affluent newport beach a city 40 miles 
southeast of los angeles said police spokesman bob oakley 
we felt a real slight rolling motion then a real abrupt 
shake it felt as if something crashed into the building it was 
that sharp oakley said a lot of alarms are going off in the 
city we had to bring in extra personnel in the communications 
center to handle hundreds of calls 
the earthquake at 107 pm measured 46 on the richter scale 
and was centered directly under newport beach according to the 
us geological survey and the california institute of technology 
in pasadena 
usgs spokeswoman pat jorgenson in menlo park said the epicenter 
was very near that of the march 10 1933 long beach earthquake 
which measured 63 on the richter scale killed 115 people and 
spurred reform of californias school construction laws 
the richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a 75 reading reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than a 65 reading 
at the san onofre nuclear power facility in northern san diego 
county the quake prompted officials to declare an unusual 
event the lowestlevel emergency declaration said southern 
california edison spokeswoman becky sordelet however the one 
nuclear reactor that was operating was not shut down 
nancy aldon of newport beach said the quake toppled books 
dishes and videotapes off shelves in her home 
the whole building shook a kind of rolling shake said 
kimberly stewart 25 who works in a law office in a 15floor 
office building in huntington beach which is adjacent to newport 
beach 
it startled everyone she said it was slight then got 
stronger and slight again we are on the 11th floor so im sure it 
seemed a lot stronger 
it was like being stopped at a stop sign and being run into 
a resident of irvine in orange county told knxam radio 
at a california newspaper publishers association seminar and 
luncheon at the grand hotel near disneyland in anaheim those in 
attendance felt a jolt and then shaking that gradually gathered 
strength chandeliers began to dance and glasses rattled on tables 
andrea schulte a 23yearold student who was at the meeting 
said the quake started with very little noise everybody stayed 
calm nobody moved except one person because she was under a 
chandelier the building was moving and the chandeliers were 
swaying 
but in newport beach resident joseph cleary said it was a 
large jolt a big jump 
in long beach 22 miles northwest of the epicenter the quake 
was felt in high rise apartments and employees at los angeles city 
hall and downtown los angeles courts also felt the temblor 
at a hearing in superior court in downtown los angeles judge 
bruce geernaert was in the midst of delivering comments on the fear 
of death suffered by rock hudsons lover marc christian then the 
room began to sway 
is it my decision or are we shaking asked the judge 
as the swaying continued a voice from the back of the room 
called out this is a fear of death your honor and everyone 
laughed 
the judge noted for the record there has been and maybe still 
is a bit of an earthquake in progress but he continued with the 
hearing 
a quake at 35 on the richter scale quake can cause slight 
damage in its immediate area a 4 can cause moderate damage and a 
5 considerable damage a 7 is a major earthquake capable of 
widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable of 
tremendous damage 
the san francisco earthquake of 1906 which occurred before the 
richter scale was devised has been estimated at 83 on the richter 
scale 
