a record heat wave throttled southern 
california for a fourth day friday as nurses tried to keep patients 
cool in a hospital without air conditioning and anyone who could 
get away fled to the beach 
the mercury hit 100 degrees in downtown los angeles at 1 pm 
smashing the april 7 record of 88 set in 1904 downtown had a 
