offering its unsecured creditors adequate compensation 
morton e handel chairman of colecos board of directors said 
the board decided against pursuing a sale of the company on the 
grounds that maintaining coleco as an independent ongoing 
business is in the best interests of the creditors and 
shareholders 
in february the board of directors had authorized management to 
explore selling coleco as a means of solving its financial problems 
the new reorganization plan announced thursday is intended 
to satisfy the needs expressed by the unsecured creditors during 
bankruptcy proceedings in new york federal court handel stated 
the avon connbased company which makes cabbage patch dolls 
and other toys filed for protection from creditors under chapter 
11 of the federal bankruptcy laws in july 1988 
