the casino control commission voted 
unanimously friday to reject elsinores atlantis casino hotel 
application for license renewal the first such denial in new 
jerseys decadeold casino industry 
commission chairman walter read said the financially troubled 
casino failed to demonstrate the financial resources business 
ability or integrity to merit an extension of its current license 
the atlantis license expires next friday 
the conclusion is inescapable read said the esa 
elsinores shore associates has not demonstrated these if we 
were to grant relicensure these standards would be rendered 
meaningless 
elsinore shore associates is atlantis parent company 
the commission now has to decide what to do next with the 
atlantis close it down or appoint a conservator 
elsinore lawyer harry levin had asked the commissioners thursday 
to grant the license with the understanding the company could meet 
standards long enough to find a buyer the casino says any chance 
of fetching a fair price would be spoiled by a closing or 
appointment of a conservator 
levin cited the owners obligations to stockholders 
employees and creditors who are owed an estimated 2 million in 
overdue payments 
it occurs to all of us that the one certain way to make 
certain all of these entities are made whole and all constituents 
are served is to allow us to dispose of this property in a normal 
orderly fashion levin said 
elsinore president jeanne hood testified earlier in the week 
that several prospective buyers have surfaced and that a sale 
likely can be completed in coming months 
but state lawyer david arrajj told commissioners thursday that 
state gaming regulators have already given the atlantis more than 
enough leeway in allowing the company to stay in business while it 
worked through bankruptcy reorganization over the last three years 
he said elsinore merely has posted more big losses and fallen 
deeper into debt he also cited the casinos admission in testimony 
that it failed on occasion to maintain the staterequired minimum 
reserve aimed at ensuring payoff on a gamblers big winnings 
this is not the mark of an applicant possessed with sufficient 
ability to justify licensure arrajj said 
