media giant southam inc may join forces with 
torstar corp to make a foray into the newspaper and publishing 
business in the united states southams president said thursday 
there is this relationship between the two companies there is 
the ability to do something john fisher told reporters after a 
speech to the toronto society of financial analysts 
fisher said nothing definite has been planned with torstar 
which holds a 224 percent interest in southam canadas largest 
newspaper publisher based on circulation the southam family holds 
222 per cent 
in 1985 torstar which publishes the toronto star and owns 
other businesses came to southams rescue buying into the company 
and promising to vote in support of the southam board to thwart a 
takeover bid by an unidentified company the deal expires june 30 
next year 
southam may decide to make its own deals specifically in the 
newspaper commercial printing or business information fields 
fisher said 
he refused to indicate when and where acquisitions may take 
place 
the newspaper arm of the publishing firm owns 16 daily 
newspapers including the ottawa citizen the vancouver sun and the 
montreal gazette as well as about a dozen weeklies 
southam also operates southam printing ltd one of canadas 
largest commercial printers 200 coles bookstores and southam 
communications ltd 
