<TEXT>
winstonsalem nc ap a state judge issued an order friday 
blocking the acquisition of rjr nabisco inc by kohlberg kravis 
roberts amp co but rjr officials said he later limited his ruling 
to the companys assets in switzerland 
forsyth county district court judge james harrill jr issued the 
restraining order and set an april 17 hearing on a motion by swiss 
investors to block the merger 
harrill granted the order in connection with a suit filed in 
switzerland that charges the buyout hurt investors by improperly 
diminishing the value of rjr nabisco bonds 
later friday an rjr nabisco spokeswoman said the judge had 
clarified his order 
the north carolina courts clarified order holds that in light 
of a prior modification to the march 20 order by the civil court in 
basel switzerland the north carolina order does not prohibit the 
merger of rjr nabiscos assets located outside switzerland said 
spokeswoman pauline howes 
in essence they narrowed the scope of the order 
considerably she said it now applies only to assets located 
inside the country of switzerland 
rjr nabisco officials said they did not believe the court action 
would have any impact on the closing of the deal 
the record 2453 billion acquisition is expected to be 
finalized some time after an rjr nabisco shareholders meeting 
scheduled for april 27 the exact date of the closing is not yet 
known 
the swiss suit is one of several claiming the buyout 
significantly reduced the value of rjr nabisco bonds 
at least three insurance companies including jeffersonpilot 
corp metropolitan life insurance co and the insurance 
subsidiaries of itt corp have sued the company claiming the 
market value of bonds they held fell 20 percent after former 
company chairman ross johnson proposed a leveraged buyout in 
october 
johnsons proposal started the bidding war eventually won by 
kohlberg kravis roberts 
</TEXT>
